. And his uncle Lord Blicester will only provide should Freddie seduce and marry Dora Pinfold, who does Good Works in a sort of a mission over on Notting Hill. However Dora Pinfold is already entwined in a relationship with Arthur Gooding. Falling in love with the girl as is his habit, Freddie borrows a few bob to shower the Notting Hill mothers with cocoa and buns, but loses it on a bet, so he must enter an Amateur Night competition to recover his funds and woo Miss Pinfold. Unfortunately, with pianist Jos. Waterbury as his accompanist, and Cousin Egbert with a slingshot, this may be harder than it sounds, and when Arthur steps into the frame once again a confrontation is on the cards.</p>
